    <note>Xue(1) Guangde [18740] Served as a Yushi dafu under Yuandi. Genealogy based on Wang Gui's funerary inscription for Xue(1) Ying's [810] son, Jichang [3388], biographies in Renming Da cidian, and XTS, 73B.20a-32a. Before segmentation with the sons of Yi(3) [18755] into the Northern, Southern and Western branches (zu), I identify as Hedong Xue, even though the ancestral home was not established in Hezhong (Fenyin) until Yi's father moved there in ca. 264. After that point, the ancestors of Ying were all members of the Xizu and will be so identified.</note>
